	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1010 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.43]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>What kind of strategy you want? Levels 1-10 kill anything that moves in Feerott that cons white or blue.&nbsp;&nbsp;Do the Ogre BL armor quests (listed on this site).  Great exp there and the gear is worthwhile for under level 15.  When you get bored in Feerrott move to Innothule Swamp.  With the new portals that came out with PoP you can port to any newbie zone in the game easily.<br><br>Warders are fairly standard.  Barbarians get a wolf. Looks like a standard wolf.  Ogres get a brown bear.  Trolls get an alligator.  Vah Shir get a tiger.  Ikar get a scaled wolf.  They look like the standard grahpics of the same beasts.  The only difference is that the size of the warder is dependent on the level you summon it. The higher the level the bigger it gets.  Your first warder is pretty small (just a bear cub for ogres).</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
