	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174515><span id= >Angelys</span></a><br><span id=notbold>47 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.02]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm about to get EQ Gold with Luclin and PoP, and would like to create a Vah Shir BST, but have read mixed reports about them.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've not read through all of the posts here (I might not live that long!), so I'm sorry if my questions have been answered somewhere else, but here they are:<br><br>1) What is the deal with melee combat?  My current main is a SK, so I've had loads of experience with both melee and a little bit of casting and pet stuff.  I've heard bad things about the AC equipment available for BST's, so can you actually fight melee effectively up to around mid-level?<br><br>2) Grouping with a BST: Are they any use in a high-level dungeon or Plane fight?  Necros have a bad rep for groups with their high-level pets, so do BST's have the same problem?<br><br>I'm sure I'll think of more questions as time goes on, but these'll do for now.  If anyone can answer them I'd be very grateful.  I'm torn between the BST and the Warrior, and if I get too many reports about how BST's gear is lame then I'll create a Warrior, but I'll really miss my spells!<br>Thanks,<br></p>&nbsp;<br>---------------------------------------------------------------<pre><b><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=513304 target=_new>Dajmin</a></b> <span style='color: maroon;'>[52 Dark Elf Reaver]</span style='color: maroon;'></pre></td></td></tr>
