	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=151090><span id=Scholar>Naluvyen</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>43 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is a common trick, not just for your pet but for yourself, as well. For instance, at level 9 you get Minor Healing and Inner Fire. They both cost the same mana (10) but Inner Fire heals more. It only raises your AC and max HP the first time, but it gives you healing EVERY time you cast it.<br><br>The only value I've found to the Healing Spells is that if someone has cast a higher level AC/HP buff on you, then you can't cast your buf as a healing spell because it can't override the higher spell. Then you have to use the less efficient &quot;pure&quot; healing spells, or else take off the higher buf.<br><br>Growlf<br>18th lvl Vah Shir BL</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
