	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=116775><span id= >SStiletto</span></a><br><span id=notbold>57 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.41]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've been soloing in N.Karana near the gypsy camp now for a while, and have to say it's great exp and very easy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Started at two yellows into 14 and three hours later was a yellow into 17.  Basically I've been killing pincer beetles, borer beetles and scythe beetles, any of them from dark blue to yellow.  And, I've occasionally killed a giffenne or two, but since they take a lot of mana and health I don't recommend them for exp.  I'm now 19, and the exp is still good.  All of the usual downsides to the Karana's don't seem to be a problem with my Beastlord.  Animals don't aggro you, the griffs (although they con threatening) don't seem to aggro, and you can easily avoid the hill giants (kinda hard to have one &quot;sneak up&quot; on you).  I have had very little down time and great exp so far.  Just ask someone to bind you at the gypsy camp, and if you get in trouble (assuming you're not kos) run up to the guards at the tower on the hill right behind the gypsy camp and they'll save you.  Also, if you bother to loot, you can sell to the gypsies.  Basically you never have to leave your spot.  I suggest hunting all around the gypsy camp, and from the camp to the spires.  Also, I believe there is a quest with one of the gypsies for exp and faction or whatnot for giving her greater lightstones and lightstones, which you might want to look into.  Good luck, and have fun.</p>&nbsp;<br>Sashaan Ahimsa<br>Malevolent Spirits<br></td></td></tr>
