	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=116775><span id= >SStiletto</span></a><br><span id=notbold>57 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The reason Grimfeather and the Silver Griffon attack is because they are technically &quot;monsters&quot; not &quot;animals&quot; like the other griffs.&nbsp;&nbsp;I know this due to the fact that rangers and druids can not cast panic animal on either.  They are a special case.  But, I have only seen Grimfeather once in all my time in N.Karana and have yet to see the Silver Griffon, except on my boyfriends computer when he was soloing him (47 Ranger, had a very difficult time of killing him).  In other words, I wouldn't worry about the griffs, and even if you are killed, the exp at this level and in this area is easy to get back.  </p>&nbsp;<br>Sashaan Ahimsa<br>Malevolent Spirits<br></td></td></tr>
