	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=633><span id= >Zanial</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>1. Depends on what classes are in the group. At 52 I have been main tank keeping agro off a 54 rogue backstabbing.<br><br>2. Melee in a group, depends. If there was no shaman or chanter I would go the role of buffer slower. For solo I melee'd next to my pet till lvl 50, after that I found it more effecient to play cleric to my pet and dot the mob.<br><br>3. On guild raids I just send the pet in, we have so many melee that gettin close to the mob is hard. The new spells from test are not live yet so I don't get bugged for buffs.<br><br>4. See #2.<br><br>5. www.eqbeastlords.com<br><br>Jerac<br>52 Vah Shir Primalist<br>Far Seekers<br>The Rathe Server</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
