	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=15&mid=10297318009874>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=15&mid=10297318009874>RE: Beastlord Class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=15&mid=10297318009874#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 19th 12:36 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=11679><span id=Sage>Martelus</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>45 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.71]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The higher the beastlord goes, the more dependent on his pet he gets.&nbsp;&nbsp;Up until the mid-twenties the BL is ok as a tank, and good as a melee back-up.  From the mid-twenties, till about level 40 the BL can melee along side his pet fairly well.  After level 40 you will become the healer/buffer for your pet who is the tank.  The low melee damage output, along with the low AC from light/leather armor forces the need for the BL to be out of +40 MOBS melee range.  Unlike Necro/Mages/Druids, the BL can still step in and melee at these high levels, but your pet will be doing most of the melee damage +40.<br><br>I'm not to the +50 game yet, but from what I have heard, BLs are usually left out in the cold on big raids.  You will always find pick-up groups, but the big raids, people get anal-retentive about who is let in a group, and most people don't see a need for the BL.<br><br>The BL is made for soloing.  If you want to solo into the high levels, you can do it with a BL.  BL's are the most efficient class in EQ at soloing blue cons.  Druids/Necros can solo evens, yellow and low red cons more easliy than the BL.  It is more efficient for Necros/Druids to solo higher cons.  The mana needed to take out a blue con for a Necro/Druid is not much less than the mana needed for them to take out a yellow or red con.  My BL can take out half a dozen blue cons before needing to med/heal.<br><br>Sorry, can't help with any epic questions.<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
