	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=173652><span id= >Piyopiyo</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Number by number ^.^ this is my take on it so far.<br><br>1. Well like all hybrids, beasties' strength is in our versatility.&nbsp;&nbsp;With duel wield and a good pet, we aren't bad damage dealers.  Also helps to throw in DDs etc.  (at lvl 30 being able to toss in an extra 81 points now and then is a big help).  Also a backup shaman with sow and useful str/sta/dex buffs.  We don't make very good tanks however, so we sometimes have the ranger-ish problem of drawing agro and making the groups healer work too hard.<br><br>2. Beastlord is good dmg dealer, but only an OK tank.. so while you would melee always in a group, you'll often find yourself being a pet-cleric while soloing.  (Your pet is very strong btw, and heals are very efficient.. even at lvl 33) I can kill whites and yellows in OT.... Downtime is brutal though.<br><br>3.  I can't say as I'm not there yet, but I imagine we'd be backup, like most hybrids.<br><br>4.  Solo hehe...you'll laugh your butt off at lvl 15, its so easy.  As I said, we solo very well at least until 30s.  Can't attest to higher than that ^_^<br><br>5.  Me too hehe.<br><br>All in all I've enjoyed it very much so far... having never played a shaman the spells still have some novelty for me (I love shrinking my pet to the size of a doormouse).  The biggest downside is finding equipment... currently wearing more tizmak than I'd like ^_^;;  Also not having double attack makes you feel underpowered (only because I forget to count the damage my pet does).<br>Oh and btw, if you make a beastlord don't make my mistake.. in the beginning concentrate on Wisdom and maybe Agil.  I put it all into str and sta (dumb dumb dumb).<br><br>Hope that helps ^_^<br><br>~Piyopiyo, Barbie Beastie~<br>~33 - Vasealle - &lt;Tribunal of Judgement&gt;~</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
